Here's the recommended implementation using **CommunityToolkit.Mvvm** source generators:

**ProductDetailViewModel.cs**

```csharp
using CommunityToolkit.Mvvm.ComponentModel;
using CommunityToolkit.Mvvm.Input;

public partial class ProductDetailViewModel : ObservableObject
{
    [ObservableProperty]
    private string _name = string.Empty;

    [ObservableProperty]
    private decimal _price;

    [ObservableProperty]
    private bool _isAvailable;

    [RelayCommand]
    private async Task LoadAsync()
    {
        // Replace with your actual data service call
        var product = await FetchProductAsync();
        Name = product.Name;
        Price = product.Price;
        IsAvailable = product.IsAvailable;
    }

    private async Task<(string Name, decimal Price, bool IsAvailable)> FetchProductAsync()
    {
        await Task.Delay(500); // simulated network call
        return ("Widget", 29.99m, true);
    }
}
```

The source generator creates public `Name`, `Price`, `IsAvailable` properties with `PropertyChanged` notifications, and a `LoadCommand` (of type `IAsyncRelayCommand`).

**ProductDetailPage.xaml** — use compiled bindings with `x:DataType`:

```xml
<ContentPage xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui"
             xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml"
             xmlns:vm="clr-namespace:MyApp.ViewModels"
             x:DataType="vm:ProductDetailViewModel"
             x:Class="MyApp.ProductDetailPage">

    <VerticalStackLayout Padding="16" Spacing="12">
        <Label Text="{Binding Name}" FontSize="24" />
        <Label Text="{Binding Price, StringFormat='Price: {0:C2}'}" />
        <Label Text="{Binding IsAvailable, StringFormat='Available: {0}'}" />
        <Button Text="Load Product"
                Command="{Binding LoadCommand}" />
        <ActivityIndicator IsRunning="{Binding LoadCommand.IsRunning}"
                           IsVisible="{Binding LoadCommand.IsRunning}" />
    </VerticalStackLayout>
</ContentPage>
```

**Key points:**

- `[ObservableProperty]` generates the public property + `PropertyChanged` raise — no boilerplate needed.
- `[RelayCommand]` on `LoadAsync` generates `LoadCommand` with built-in `IsRunning` you can bind to for a loading indicator.
- `x:DataType` enables compiled bindings (8–20× faster, AOT-safe). Add `<WarningsAsErrors>XC0022;XC0025</WarningsAsErrors>` to your `.csproj` to catch binding errors at build time.
- Set `BindingContext` in code-behind via DI: `BindingContext = vm;`
